rue,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17435,"name":"","username":"rasteron","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rasteron/{size}/55_2.png","created_at":"2017-04-27T05:06:22.160Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThanks guys! \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e As for other media like these replacement diffuse textures, it was a quick test so I have used L3DT to generate color maps out of its base textures and the modified heightmap. I have used the Temperate climate set on this setup and apparently the license prohibits redistribution of its base textures, so I‚Äôll just find other alternatives that has either Public Domain or CC license when it is ready for PR or release.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-27T05:06:22.160Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":45,"readers_count":44,"score":9.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3052,"topic_slug":"terrain-color-and-detail-map","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":54,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17436,"name":"","username":"rasteron","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rasteron/{size}/55_2.png","created_at":"2017-04-27T05:07:03.672Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"3052\" data-full=\"true\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/40/1123_1.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e Modanung:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOur Flintstone-mobile would maybe require an upgrade then. I agree it‚Äôs prettier, but quite a bit more hilly too.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ehaha nice one \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/smiley.png?v=5\" title=\":smiley:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":smiley:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-27T05:07:03.672Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":46,"readers_count":45,"score":9.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":3052,"topic_slug":"terrain-color-and-detail-map","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Modanung","name":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":54,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17452,"name":"","username":"rasteron","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rasteron/{size}/55_2.png","created_at":"2017-04-27T13:52:21.972Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"smellymumbler\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"3052\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/ad7895/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e smellymumbler:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHoly crap, that‚Äôs awesome! \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/smiley.png?v=10\" title=\":smiley:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":smiley:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCan the detail map be added on a per channel basis? I mean, one detail for grass, another for rock, another for sand, etc.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThanks \u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/smellymumbler\"\u003e@smellymumbler\u003c/a\u003e! \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=10\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e Yes with some tweaks I think this is also possible.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-27T13:52:21.972Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":43,"readers_count":42,"score":18.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":3052,"topic_slug":"terrain-color-and-detail-map","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":54,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17459,"name":"Jonathan","username":"Sinoid","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/f19dbf/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-04-27T18:49:45.288Z","cooked":"\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCan the detail map be added on a per channel basis? I mean, one detail for grass, another for rock, another for sand, etc.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou can pack grayscale maps into channels of an RGBA texture and get the mixed value pretty easily.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003evec4 blend = texture2D(BlendMap, texCoords).rgba;\nvec4 detVal = texture2D(PackedDetailTextures, texCoords * DetailScalingFactor).rgba;\nfloat dotValue = dot(detVal, blend);\nfloat sVal = 1.0 - (dotValue * 2.0);\noColor += (-sVal);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLight-weight enough that you could also get an analytic normal from it with additional samples.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-27T18:49:45.288Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":18.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3052,"topic_slug":"terrain-color-and-detail-map","display_username":"Jonathan","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":669,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17460,"name":"","username":"smellymumbler","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/ad7895/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-04-27T19:34:56.325Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWhere would \u003ccode\u003ePackedDetailTextures\u003c/code\u003e come from? I imagine i have a single texture, a splatmap, where each channel contains a different material definition: sand, grass, rock and snow (R, G, B, A). I use those as masks to apply 4 different channels in my terrain. Each material contains 4 textures: diffuse, specular, normal and detail.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-27T19:34:56.325Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":10,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":13.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3052,"topic_slug":"terrain-color-and-detail-map","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Sinoid","name":"Jonathan","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/f19dbf/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":674,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17462,"name":"Jonathan","username":"Sinoid","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/f19dbf/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-04-27T19:38:41.802Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThey‚Äôre grayscale detail-texture maps for each blend channel, not materials - completely different thing from detail-mapping.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-27T19:38:41.802Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":11,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":38,"readers_count":37,"score":17.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":3052,"topic_slug":"terrain-color-and-detail-map","display_username":"Jonathan","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"smellymumbler","name":"","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/ad7895/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":669,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17463,"name":"","username":"smellymumbler","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/ad7895/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-04-27T22:45:48.856Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"onebox whitelistedgeneric\"\u003e\n  \u003cheader class=\"source\"\u003e\n      \u003cimg src=\"https://slot1-images.wikia.nocookie.net/__cb1589447383916/common/skins/common/images/favicon.ico\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\"\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://urho3d.fandom.com/wiki/Expand_default_terrain_material_to_6_textures_using_the_six_primary\u0026amp;secondary_colors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eUrho3D Wiki\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/header\u003e\n  \u003carticle class=\"onebox-body\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/315;\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/urho3d/images/d/d9/Terrain_6splat-0.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20150305072039\" class=\"thumbnail\" width=\"690\" height=\"315\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://urho3d.fandom.com/wiki/Expand_default_terrain_material_to_6_textures_using_the_six_primary\u0026amp;secondary_colors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eExpand default terrain material to 6 textures using the six...\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHere I'm using the \"six basic colors\" red, yellow, green, cyan, blue and magenta to get six separate color weight. Urho is currently per default limited to five textures. You need to modify the file \"Source/Urho3D/Graphics/GraphicsDefs.h\" first to...\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n  \u003c/article\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"onebox-metadata\"\u003e\n    \n    \n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"clear: both\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLike that? So, if i want specular/normal, i just have to load up more texture units and load the respective maps?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-27T22:45:48.856Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":37,"readers_count":36,"score":27.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":3052,"topic_slug":"terrain-color-and-detail-map","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://urho3d.fandom.com/wiki/Expand_default_terrain_material_to_6_textures_using_the_six_primary\u0026secondary_colors","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Expand default terrain material to 6 textures using the six primary\u0026secondary colors | Urho3D Wiki | Fandom","clicks":5}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":674,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":17465,"name":"","username":"Victor","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/v/3e96dc/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-04-27T23:14:47.630Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYou can also use texture arrays to allow for more textures. \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/wink.png?v=10\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wink:\"\u003e You can do this manually (send a large texture to the shader which contains multiple textures), or using the TextureArray feature.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"2695\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jtippetts1/40/96_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/how-to-use-texture2darray/2695/2\"\u003eHow to use Texture2DArray?\u003c/a\u003e \u003ca class=\"badge-wrapper  bullet\" href=\"/c/discussions/support/10\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"badge-category-parent-bg\" style=\"background-color: #25AAE2;\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"badge-category-bg\" style=\"background-color: #92278F;\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category clear-badge\" title=\"Someone can help you.\"\u003eSupport\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cblockquote\u003e\n    I use it in my custom terrain shader to provide 8 (or more) different terrain detail textures. \nIn GLSL: \nuniform sampler2DArray sDetailMap2; \nThen, in the pixel shader, to sample it use: \ntexture(sDetailMap2, vec3(vDetailTexCoord.xz, 1)); // To index texture at array location 1 \nIn HLSL: \nTexture2DArray tDetailMap : register(t2);; \nSamplerState sDetailMap : register(s2); \nIn pixel shader: \ntDetailMap.Sample(sDetailMap, float3(iDetailTexCoord.xz, 0)); // To index texture at array location 0 \nThe‚Ä¶\n  \u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n","post_number":14,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-27T23:14:47.630Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":13,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":35,"readers_count":34,"score":32.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3052,"topic_slug":"terrain-color-and-detail-map","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://disc